issue.title: Added contributors in readme
issue.body:
# Intro

Looking back on my decision to add these six lines to the contributors file, my thought process began by attempting to re-imagine the format of the readme file. Thinking that a mere one heading just wasn't sufficient to express the scope and magnitude of this project, I conceptualized a revolutionary second heading consisting of a few essential sub points.
## The Second Header

My important second heading took a new perspective on describing this project. I thought that the members of this nascent, but thriving community would enjoy more recognition than simply appearing in a list of emails. By adding the github usernames of members of this growing open source collective, I aimed to increase the visibility of our peers within this community. 
## Future Additions

In the future, I plan to update the readme file with a list of top contributors using a simple algorithm of weighted commits and accepted pull requests. By adding this leaderboard we'll create a central listing of the most trusted members of the community, allowing old and new members alike to know which others to seek out when questions or requests arise. 
## Conclusions

Synergy.
